This paper deals with resource allocation for device-to-device (D2D) communications in 5G networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (NI) in computer science. The paper also proposes a game-theoretic approach to optimize the social utility of D2D players, which falls under the category of game theory (GT). Additionally, the paper discusses partial channel state information (CSI) and proposes algorithms to address this issue, which relates to information theory (IT) and systems and control (SY). Finally, the paper includes simulation results, which could be considered as multimedia (MM) in computer science.
